 :tx/rationale "ADR-FOUNDATION-033: LOAD-BEARING FAILURE DETECTION. Not all failures are equal. Some are bugs (low information, fix and move on). Others are load-bearing — they reveal structural truths that success would have hidden. The PERF-1 failure (misdiagnosed store loading) was load-bearing: it revealed reflexive divergence, the introspective observer, and the Y-combinator framing. None of these would have emerged from a successful implementation. MECHANISM: Three types of learning triggered by different failure signatures. Type 1 (calibration): prediction error is random, decreasing with data. Action: adjust weights. Type 2 (structure): prediction error is systematic, persisting across hypotheses. Action: reorganize model (FEGH bridges). Type 3 (ontology): failure doesn't fit ANY existing divergence type. Action: ontological inquiry (what category of knowledge is missing?). DETECTION: When per-type hypothesis accuracy is consistently low (mean error > 0.5 across 10+ hypotheses), escalate from Type 1 to Type 2. When a failure mode doesn't match Types 1-9, escalate to Type 3. TRIGGER: anomalous failure = a hypothesis outcome that doesn't fit any existing failure pattern. SURFACE: flag to user as potentially load-bearing. This IS the meta-cognitive skill that made Session 038 productive — noticing that the failure to diagnose correctly was itself informative. FORMALIZATION: aleatoric surprise (noise, ignore) vs epistemic surprise (signal, investigate). The distinction: epistemic surprise is SYSTEMATIC and doesn't decrease with more data. TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-030, ADR-FOUNDATION-032, INV-FOUNDATION-014."
